volume.name: Pete the P.O.'d Postal Worker: Pete's Very Special Christmas
Around the World with Huckleberry and His Friends

description: A short comic book story about an old woman with nothing to lose. Written by Juliana Azevedo and illustrated by Mauricio Pommella.
Deco and Pascale meet the enigmatic Elsepeth and friendly Jovian, and go on their real first shopping trip since their arrival in The Archives.
A series of violently cruel murders attracts the attention of the local police. Could they have anything to do with the myth of the Slavic demon? Who should be afraid and who can sleep peacefully?

The classic comic series featuring the art of Joe Kubert! Issue #2 from the 1940s, the Black Cat! The Black Cat was one of the earliest female costumed crime-fighters in the comics, debuting in 1941 in POCKET COMICS. Linda Turner was a Hollywood starlet and former stunt-woman in the early 1940's when she battled her director who she suspected of being a Nazi spy.

Story Titles

  • Who Is the Black Cat?
  • Banker's Holiday
  • The Rampaging Reporters
  • Bang! Bang! Went the Trolley
  • Gabriel Blows His Horn

In the rubble of Project Zephyr, the 'Nado Ninjas discover a battered Cale Isaacs and the remnants of his team. Together, they devise a plan to stop Hurricane Brandon once and for all - a Storm that now covers half of the northern hemisphere. Its center located directly above Wyoming.

Note: The digital edition (12/31/2014) for this issue was released before the print edition.

Five realms. Five princesses. Zero men. The noose begins to tighten around Evanfar, from Barra and Ilina's armies as well as from within, as Bethany's kingdom crumbles without the strength of her leadership. However, Bethany has far more stunning revelations to deal with-as she comes face to face with her treacherous mother Valeria-the Queen of Shadows!

name: Fear

description: After last issue's surprise ending, can Ellison Maximillan be trusted? What's going on at the Kane Institute? Can Dr. Benson help Blaze control his powers and is Carl okay? What's delivered in the mail that has Harlan so surprised? And just what's the deal with this flying misanthrope that has his sights set directly on Fist of Justice?

Shards

Melbourne City stands as a glowing testament to our ever expanding technological innovation and evolution as a species. This sprawling metropolis now covers the extents of what was once the entire state of Victoria. Sectorised communities and corporate governance protect and pamper to the rich, whilst the less fortunate are left to feed off the dregs left behind So many stories and tales to be told, playing out against backdrop of steel, concrete, glass and neon. Down amongst it all Gabe tackles the cybernetic mercenary, Snare in an effort to get answers to the truth behind the kidnappings.
name: Shards

description:
'To Become A Monster' Part Two

Freddie's war stories cause Bobby to begin investigating what is really happening to his brother.

Freddie runs into trouble with more British agents, then quickly earns several new bullet holes in his hoodie.
name: To Become A Monster Part Two

description: What if all your wishes for revenge came true? And came in the form of three snake-haired, blood-spitting vengeance goddesses? Wouldn't that be kind of awesome? In the second book of the series, it's time for Lelaina Pentheus to stop whining and start controlling her growing powers.
name: Book 2

description:
Birth of the Cool Part II

Return to the Harlem Renaissance! Witness for yourself the birth of the cool...the emergence of the super-hip street avenger...The Harlem Shadow! Read two separate, self contained adventures concerning YEAR ONE of Harlem's masked marauder. "Giselle" is the story of an abused wife who has been pushed to the edge and decides to call on The Harlem Shadow. "The Midnight Sun" tells the story of how Harlem's number one black news publication is going to handle their reporting of NYC's new phenomenon...a black, masked vigilante!!!
name: Birth of the Cool Part II

description: Jack tries to adjust to his life out West, but new enemies witness Jack hit an impossible target and realize he is a threat to their plans. In a dream, a dark omen reminds Jack of the broken vow he'd made to his mentor, but he soon awakens to a true nightmare.

Found

In modern London, The Eternal Children find Wendy Darling and James Hook.

In the 17th century, James Hook becomes the first Lost Boy.
name: Found

person_credits.name: Paul Belliveau
person_credits.role: writer, editor, artist, letterer, cover, other

description: Who is the "Blob" and what secrets he has? A short story between issues 1 and 2. A very important chapter. Don't miss it!
Do you want to build a snowman? You'll regret it! Plus: A festive edition of fish flicks!

Smitty has lost everything twice-over, and now nothing is out of bounds as he desperately seeks a score large enough to buy his way back to safety. His former crewmate, now a feared captain, means to ensure Smitty's continued misery, instead. They can't both succeed.

Note: The digital edition (12/31/2014) for this issue was released before the print edition.

The Little Black Samurai Boy

After taking on an apprentice, Daiki now embarks on a his training. When faced with extending his skills to the ENTIRE nomad village, his motives come into question as to what is means to be samurai. As all samurai do, he takes on the problem HEAD ON. After the lesson Daiki and his apprentice are confronted with a situation that not only tests their overall skills, but extremely chance the dynamic on not only them but those around them. Events that will change their lives forever.
name: The Little Black Samurai Boy

description:
Mercy comes in many forms.

Life in the stalag is taking its toll. Joe Human has withstood Mengele's attempts to break him, but how much longer can he hold out when even his own people turn against him? Long enough, perhaps, to learn a secret that could change the very nature of the war. If only he could inform Earth Command...

Animus

Menace returns to the 21st centry with Animus so he may take his revenge and get Kokoro's necklace. Kokoro meets a hooded man that Frank does not trust, but may be the key to unleashing Kokoro's power.
name: The Little Black Samurai Boy

description:
The Weight of the Matter Part 1

The Trouble and Kid Fury return to the scene of a previous adventure, but what will they find? Whatever it is, things are about to get serious in Capital City.
name: The Weight of the Matter Part 1

description: Yaya gives her costuming skills a test run at a convention in Atlanta, but things are off to a rough start. When she has a run-in with another cosplayer, Yaya must try to resist the urge to unleash her superpowers.

person_credits.name: Jim Davis
person_credits.role: writer, artist, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

description:
Alphabetical Disorder for Andy

Andy loves the most popular girl in school, Bethany. In this issue Andy faces the oppressive rule of alphabetical order in the classroom. Andy takes on the school board to win the heart of his true love. Will he overthrow this tyrannical regime or will he be sent to the gallows?
name: Alphabetical Disorder For Andy

description:
By popular demand, Sadie and Robin return in a special seasonal sequel to "Before You Go"!

It's the holiday season, and Sadie, Robin's cheerful and affectionate girlfriend, is suddenly quiet and withdrawn. Can Robin get to the bottom of this surprising change and salvage their budding relationship?

Can love exist in the depths of hell? In the beginning the fallen angels of Heaven make a new empire that they call "The Dark". But there are some unfinished relationships that were severed in this departure. The Cat goddess Bast, and the dark lord Anubus have a secret that they aren't sharing with Lucifer. This origin story arc of how how the Egyptian cat-god Blinth was born and why his place in The Dark has always been unstable, and why he hates Lucifer so much.

Krusnik Keep has been hunting his vampire for 300 years. Wishing to end it once and for all, he kills his vampire and watches him turn to ash. But he discovers all has not gone to plan, when he returns home to find he is still immortal and can sense the lingering presence of his vampire. What has happened, and what role does it play in the lives of former familiar Soosa and the Krusnik of his once master, the vampire Endless? Fraught emotions are brought to the fore while ghosts need to be laid to their final rest... Be sure to read the first book of this series, "Dark Crimson and a Shade of White"!

Chapter Titles

  • Prologue
  • Chapter 1: The Dawn of Awakening
  • Chapter 2: Krusnik
  • Chapter 3: Faust
  • Chapter 4: Prison of Light
  • Chapter 5: Dawnbreaker
  • Epilogue
name: Vol. 1

volume.name: Dark Green And A Dream of Silver

description: Grayson Goode begins his paranormal investigations as the killer known only as Ripper reeks havoc upon the inhabitants of Victorian London. Meanwhile the devious Ringmaster plots some heinous criminal act but just who or what is helping him?

"Have we met before?" Bryony slaps her lover's face the moment she hears those heartless words. Five months ago, she fell in love with CEO Rafael, who came to buy her island. They spent an incredible time together, but afterward they lost contact with each other. When she found out that she was pregnant, Bryony began to fear that Rafael seduced her to get her property. Hoping to see him at a party, Bryony gathers up her courage to crash it?but she can't believe her ears when she finds out the truth. He claims that he has lost all memory of her from a plane crash accident!
name: Pregnancy & Passion I

description:
The Punishment for Cutting Class

Former CIA and superhero, current single mother Paola Cruz-Randall is just trying to pay the rent while raising her two teenagers with special powers of their own.
name: The Punishment for Cutting Class

description:
Darkness

An evil thought only to be fairy tale has returned! A young girl, Arana and several others must find a way to stop this nightmare of creatures before the First World falls into ultimate darkness.

The First World is a sword and sorcery adventure unlike any you have ever seen! What makes it so different? There are no chosen ones, no destined savior. There isn't one special thing to accomplish and then BOOM, the world is saved!
name: Darkness

description: Five Star Banquet is a collection of 5 comic strip series by cartoonist James Mar. The comic titles are as follows: Animal Time, The Ma Family, Instant Kung Fu Girl, Bryan and Anita, and Johnny "Dai" Goh. The genres range from humor to romance. "Animal Time" was James' first foray into comic strips and, at the time, was run in USC's Daily Trojan. The rest of the comic strips are influenced by James' Chinese heritage.

Awakening

Raven Alice Moon's days as a combat medic in Afghanistan are behind her. But New York is harboring a terrifying secret that will have her facing an enemy unlike any she's faced before.
name: Awakening

description:
When Brains Collide!

Lionheart, the feline investigative reporter, returns to action when a cast of oddballs forces him into their ill-considered battle to prevent an alien invasion. Possessed appliances, talking brains, battling robots and the world's most powerful shrew unite to face the most unlikely enemy of all.
name: When Brains Collide!

description:
Journey with the Wandering Stars! Seven mathematicians from various eras in history who are mysteriously banded together to take on problems of a grand and metaphysical nature!

Following an unexpected visit from the White Rabbit, the creative abilities of our cosmic crusaders are put to the test when they're thrust into the middle of a devastating skirmish between the absurdly playful Wonderland and the geometrically composed Flatland.

Can the Wandering Stars broker peace between these two vastly different realms?

All this and more in this exciting volume of MATHEMAGICK!

volume.name: Mathemagick: The War of Flat and Wonder

description: Not letting her blindness get the better of her, Celia enjoys life to the fullest, doing whatever catches her interest-from scuba diving to managing her own company. Her boyfriend, Francesco, is beside himself with worry about her, and out of his misguided love he tries to hold her back. "I'm not handicapped, and I don't need your pity! Why won't you let me live my life?" In a moment of recklessness, they hurt each other deeply, and decide to go their separate ways. Do two people need more than love to be able to share their lives together? Read the conclusion of this series of romances about six Italian brothers!
name: Vol. 1

description: Dominic is the CEO of the international automotive maker Moretti Motors. An attractive man, he's famous for being a shrewd businessman and playboy. His brilliant secretary, Angelina, has secretly admired him for years, but currently she has much bigger concerns. Her younger brother, Renni, has gotten himself into trouble, and is being blackmailed for Moretti Motors company secrets-secrets that only Angelina can provide. Ultimately she decides to help her brother, but soon her betrayals are discovered by Dominic himself...
name: Moretti's Legacy III

description:
Heresy has come to The City Of The Ever Open Eye. Through every crack and crevice, an alien sect has bubbled up in order to poison the youth, corrupt the dead and make mockery of ancient tradition. Join Mr Unpronounceable - homeless necromancer - as he becomes embroiled in a multidimensional conspiracy that is quite beyond his capacity to deal with.

Insect Priests, Shambling Ghouls, Mandrill Philosophers, Domestic Demons, Ectoplasmic Monkeys, and Shrivelled Homunculi abound in this surreal second volume of Mr Unpronounceable tales from cult author and psychedelic fantasy artist, Tim Molloy.

first_appearance_locations.name: The City Of The Ever Open Eye

location_credits.name: The City Of The Ever Open Eye

volume.name: Mr Unpronounceable and the Sect of the Bleeding Eye

description:
In ancient times Gods and Goddesses walked the mortal realm in search of battle, glory and adoration. They revelled in their power and dominated the lands, becoming known by many names from many cultures. Only one thing remained constant; their raw power and ability to inspire change.

The Gods' time however was passing. Humanity grew ever stronger and moved away from their Deities. Many of the ancient gods fell into quiet slumber, waiting for a time when the world would have need of them again. Only one was left as guardian - Badbh, the Goddess of Death.

The world turned and humanity continued to grow in the Gods' absence. Badbh stood proud in her duty and watched quietly, never interfering in man's progress. That was until the day the world's balance was disrupted. The day the War God Neit awakened.

Seeing that Badbh had weakened from her long vigil and how corrupt man had become, Neit set about conquering the mortal realm. He would become the only true god and crush all beneath his will. He would see man cast into the underworld and the Earth burn for humanity's arrogance.

Badbh, knowing her power had grown weak, turned to the only one strong enough to oppose him. She awakens the Goddess Nemhain from her slumber, gifting her a mortal shell to once again walk the land of the living as its last hope to avert disaster....
name: Vol. 1

description: Jack Boxer is a retired prohibition-era Chicago cop who finds himself attempting to navigate 1950s Los Angeles.

Pewfell in For The Love of Hornbag. Pewfell Comic Numbers 5-8 Omnibus Edition

He can't get any respect as a wizard, but all Pewfell really wants is a quite life of domestic bliss. Destiny, however, has other plans. Join Pewfell as he gets thrown out of his house by a gang of feminist gnomes, runs afoul of a brainwashing cult, and gets banished to an extremely bizarre dimension with very little in the way of clothing.

Pewfell is written, illustrated and published by Chuck Whelon, with additional material by occasional co-writer Adam Prosser. This volume contains some material that may be inappropriate for younger readers and is rated 17+

This second volume is a compilation of issues #5-8 of the Pewfell comic book series. It forms a complete and self-contained tale and is 116 full color pages.
name: Volume 2

volume.name: Pewfell: For the Love of Hornbag

description: Eden is a newspaper reporter hired to cover the famous, charismatic race car driver Rafal Santini. The sexy Italian, with his dark, flowing hair, has captured the attention of many, and was Eden's lover four years ago...until Eden was pulled into a heinous plot involving his wealthy but greedy family. He didn't believe a word I said and drove me from the country, calling me filthy names. But when they meet again, his eyes are brimming with blatant desire for her.
name: Monte Carlo Affair III

description:
The Gest of Robyn Hode

Robin and his merry band scour the town of Sherwood for medical supplies to steal, and give them to those in need.
name: The Gest of Robyn Hode

volume.name: Robin Hood: Outlaw of the 21st Century

description:
No Songs Strong Enough

Salvage specialist Captain Jayson Wilraven finds his life and the lives of his crew in peril when a strange charterer wants a mysterious sunken vessel hidden, not raised-and sends armed mercenaries to make sure his orders are followed. Meanwhile, Jon Andreden's trial of an underwater smart machine is disrupted by a weird organic submersible. His life is soon turned dangerously upside down when he meets its creator, the beautiful Laeina, who recruits him to help find her missing sister...
name: No Songs Strong Enough

description: Follow the adventures of Fil and Mantis, an all ages story about two best friends trying to find their place in a galaxy filled with aliens, bounty hunters, robots, faceless drones, and an overbearing boss.

volume.name: Spaced Out! The Story of Fil & Mantis

description:
RABBI'S LAMENT

Rabbi Solomon Rotblatt is called in the middle of the night for an urgent matter regarding a prominent citizen of the city. The urgent matter - to exorcise the demon of a possessed man. He is followed...by good and evil. The news he receives from the possessed man will shape the events to come. A rabbi performing exorcisms? What/Who is SPIRALMIND? What about the werewolves? Yes, werewolves! Find out all this and more in this Phi3 COMICS' premier issue - SPIRALMIND #1: RABBI'S LAMENT
name: Rabbi's Lament

description:
The Twenty-Fourth Floor

Introducing TransCat: America's first transgender superhero! (Well, maybe not the first but, at the very least, the first who is the lead character of her own ongoing series!)

Follow TransCat's first high-flying adventure as she discovers her powers and does battle with voyeuristic upskirt photographers at her local comic convention! What fun!
name: The Twenty-Fourth Floor

description: After meeting and falling head over heels in love with Ryan, a millionaire, Kelly drops out of college and becomes his fiancee. But his family doesn't like her because she is not of their social class and they conspire to break them up. Ryan's brother even attacks her while she's pregnant! Narrowly escaping the attack, Kelly runs to Ryan, but he accuses her of seducing his brother. He calls off the engagement, writes her a goodbye check and leaves her in despair. Feeling as though she can't trust anyone, Kelly disappears from Ryan's life.
name: Pregnancy & Passion II

description: As Jubilee learns more about her new vampire heritage from Raizo Kodo and the Forgiven, the X-Men fight to rescue Jubilee from the hands of her bloodsucking brethren! But when the Marvel Universe's deadliest assassins arrive, hired to kill every member of the Forgiven, the three-way battle quickly spirals out of control! Guest-starring Lady Bullseye, the Assassin's Guild and Lord Deathstrike! Plus: A squad of lost Skrulls infiltrates the X-Men, and Pixie is taken hostage - or did she go by choice? Collects X-Men (2010) #24-29.
name: Volume 6

description: This volume skewers illegal road-racing, superheroes, and westerns in a series of satirical misadventures that include bungling aliens and fascist bunnies armed with automatic rifles.
name: Vol. 1
